PN,31201
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,FThere is "no evidence that attention
OL,7,Fdeficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD)
OL,8,Fis overdiagnosed in the UK" and the
OL,9,Fcondition could even be
OL,10,F"underdiagnosed", a team of experts
OL,11,Fhas said.
OL,13,FBut they conceded that some people may
OL,14,Fhave been misdiagnosed with the
OL,15,Fcondition.
OL,26,@nD@JOUpD@[O]rD@AOUrD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,FA team of 32 experts from around the
OL,7,FUK including clinicians, academics and
OL,8,Fpatients warned that the main issue
OL,9,Fsurrounding ADHD is that services
OL,10,F"cannot adequately support" people who
OL,11,Fneed help.
OL,13,FAnd "alarmist" rhetoric around the
OL,14,Fcondition could "deny" people care,
OL,15,Fthey added.
OL,17,FThe new paper, published in the
OL,18,FBritish Journal of Psychiatry, points
OL,19,Fout that around one in 20 children
OL,20,F(5.4%) and 3.3% of adults are
OL,21,Festimated to have ADHD.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@[O]uD@EOUuD@NO]vD@QOUvD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,FThe authors highlight how health
OL,7,Frecords show a rise in the rate of
OL,8,Factual diagnosis of the condition in
OL,9,Fclinical services between 2000 and
OL,10,F2018.
OL,12,FBut they point out that while this has
OL,13,Fincreased, the data suggests it is
OL,14,Fstill "substantially below the ADHD
OL,15,Fpopulation prevalence in the UK,
OL,16,Fproviding no evidence at present that
OL,17,FADHD is overdiagnosed at a population
OL,18,Flevel".
OL,26,@vD@GOUzD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,FThey said this increase in diagnoses
OL,7,Fmade in clinical services may be
OL,8,Flinked to heightened awareness of the
OL,9,Fcondition.
OL,11,F"There is no evidence that ADHD is
OL,12,Fover-diagnosed in the UK. Indeed,
OL,13,Favailable data point to under-
OL,14,Fdiagnosis," they wrote.
OL,16,F"The main issue is that UK clinical
OL,17,Fservices cannot adequately support
OL,18,Findividuals with ADHD who need help.
OL,26,@sD@AOUvD@KO]xD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,F"There is a risk that the narrative
OL,7,Fclaiming 'ADHD is over-diagnosed'
OL,8,Fcould be used to deny people with
OL,9,Fproperly-diagnosed ADHD the care they
OL,10,Fdeserve."
OL,12,FBut they add: "Some cases may be
OL,13,Fmisdiagnosed due to low-quality
OL,14,Fassessment, poor adherence to national
OL,15,Fguidance, or inappropriate
OL,16,Fdifferential diagnosis."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@IO]tD@OOUxD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,FMeanwhile, in addition to
OL,7,Fmisdiagnosis, they said there has been
OL,8,Fa tendency over time to recognise more
OL,9,F"mild" ADHD cases, and they point out
OL,10,Fthat more work is needed in this field.
OL,12,FLead author Professor Samuele Cortese,
OL,13,Ffrom the University of Southampton,
OL,14,Ftold the Press Association: "Every
OL,15,Ftime there is a discussion around the
OL,16,Fprevalence of ADHD and how it is
OL,17,Fdiagnosed, the focus of the
OL,18,Fconversation most of the time is
OL,19,Faround the fact that the diagnosis
OL,20,Frate has increased over time.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@FO]vD@]OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,F"Sometimes it's described in an
OL,7,Falarmistic tone.
OL,9,F"What we wanted to highlight in this
OL,10,Fpiece is that after reviewing all the
OL,11,Fevidence we were aware of ` in the UK
OL,12,Fin particular, but also comparing to
OL,13,Finternational estimates ` the
OL,14,Fconclusion is that it is true that the
OL,15,Fdiagnosis rates have increased.
OL,17,F"So we are diagnosing more ADHD in the
OL,18,Fpast decade, but there are still many
OL,19,Fwith ADHD who are out there but
OL,20,Fdespite this they're not diagnosed.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,F"So certainly this increase means that
OL,7,Fthere is more awareness now. But the
OL,8,Fproblem is that we are not yet meeting
OL,9,Fthe need of these people."
OL,11,FHe added: "Certainly we acknowledge,
OL,12,Fof course, that another issue is that
OL,13,Fprobably some who have received a
OL,14,Fdiagnosis of ADHD, probably they don't
OL,15,Fhave ADHD ` they are misdiagnosed with
OL,16,Fother things.
OL,18,F"But overall, the situation is such
OL,19,Fthat still there is an unmet need for
OL,20,Fthese people.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@ZO]sD@KOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,F"And this is quite concerning, of
OL,7,Fcourse, because if not treated
OL,8,Fproperly, ADHD exposes to significant
OL,9,Frisk for the individual and their
OL,10,Ffamily."
OL,12,FProf Cortese said these risks include
OL,13,Faccidental injuries, traumatic
OL,14,Finjuries, car accidents, suicide,
OL,15,Fsubstance misuse and increased risk of
OL,16,Fdeath.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,FCo-author on the paper, Professor
OL,7,FTamsin Ford, head of the Department of
OL,8,FPsychiatry at the University of
OL,9,FCambridge, said: "While many more
OL,10,Fpeople with ADHD are being recognised
OL,11,Fand treated, we are failing to support
OL,12,Fmany more.
OL,14,F"Overdiagnosis is not a problem, but
OL,15,Fmisdiagnosis may be as people are
OL,16,Fdriven into the private sector by long
OL,17,Fwaits; and sadly, missed diagnoses
OL,18,Fremain common."
OL,26,@qD@ROUvD@AOUzD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,FIn December the Government launched a
OL,7,Freview into ADHD, autism and mental
OL,8,Fhealth services.
OL,10,FOfficials said they want to examine
OL,11,Frising demand for services and "what
OL,12,Fis driving it".
OL,14,FSpeaking at the time, Health Secretary
OL,15,FWes Streeting said: "We must look at
OL,16,Fthis through a strictly clinical lens
OL,17,Fto get an evidence-based understanding
OL,18,Fof what we know, what we don't know,
OL,19,Fand what these patterns tell us about
OL,20,Four mental health system, autism and
OL,21,FADHD services.
OL,26,@sD@`OUtD@NO]wD@UOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772824283
OL,3,C'No evidence ADHD is overdiagnosed in
OL,4,Cthe UK'
OL,6,F"That's the only way we can ensure
OL,7,Feveryone gets timely access to
OL,8,Faccurate diagnosis and effective
OL,9,Fsupport."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@IO]
